---
const items = [
  {
    title: 'Where your biochemistry stands now',
    body: 'A current read on functional markers, including those often linked to energy, nutrients, and muscle, useful context as you and your clinician consider GLP-1.',
    icon: 'balance',
  },
  {
    title: 'The genetics that are relevant',
    body: 'We report on clinically relevant variations that relate to how your body handles nutrients and detox pathways, not a sprawling, alarming gene report.',
    icon: 'dna',
  },
  {
    title: 'Explained in plain language',
    body: 'A complete report you can actually read, so you walk into your provider conversation informed rather than overwhelmed.',
    icon: 'report',
  },
];
---

<section class="section prec">
  <div class="container prec__grid">
    <div class="prec__intro">
      <p class="eyebrow" data-reveal>How the report reads</p>
      <h2 class="prec__title" data-reveal style="--reveal-delay: 0.06s">
        Biomarkers and genetics, read together.
      </h2>
      <p class="prose prec__lede" data-reveal style="--reveal-delay: 0.12s">
        Combined, the two layers give a clearer baseline than either alone, the kind of
        context that makes a GLP-1 plan personal rather than generic.
      </p>
    </div>

    <ol class="prec__list" data-stagger>
      {items.map((it) => (
        <li class="cap">
          <span class="cap__icon" aria-hidden="true">
            {it.icon === 'balance' && (
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path d="M12 3v18M5 7h14M5 7l-2.5 6a3 3 0 0 0 5 0L5 7zM19 7l-2.5 6a3 3 0 0 0 5 0L19 7zM8 21h8" />
              </svg>
            )}
            {it.icon === 'dna' && (
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path d="M7 3c0 6 10 6 10 12M17 3c0 6-10 6-10 12M7 3h10M7 21h10M8 7h8M8 17h8" />
              </svg>
            )}
            {it.icon === 'report' && (
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path d="M6 2h8l4 4v16H6zM14 2v4h4M9 13l2 2 4-4" />
              </svg>
            )}
          </span>
          <div class="cap__text">
            <h3 class="cap__h">{it.title}</h3>
            <p class="cap__b">{it.body}</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .prec__grid { display: grid; gap: var(--sp-6); }
  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .prec__grid { grid-template-columns: 0.85fr 1.15fr; gap: var(--sp-8); align-items: start; }
    .prec__intro { position: sticky; top: 100px; }
  }
  .prec__title { font-size: var(--step-2); margin: var(--sp-3) 0 var(--sp-4); }
  .prec__lede { color: var(--muted); }

  .prec__list { display: grid; }
  .cap {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: var(--sp-4);
    align-items: start;
    padding-block: var(--sp-5);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
  }
  .cap:first-child { border-top: 0; padding-top: 0; }
  .cap:last-child { padding-bottom: 0; }
  .cap__icon {
    display: inline-grid; place-items: center;
    width: 46px; height: 46px; border-radius: 12px;
    color: var(--jade);
    background: oklch(82% 0.155 158 / 0.1);
    border: 1px solid oklch(82% 0.155 158 / 0.22);
  }
  .cap__icon svg { width: 23px; height: 23px; }
  .cap__h { font-size: var(--step-1); margin-bottom: var(--sp-2); }
  .cap__b { color: var(--muted); max-width: 52ch; }
</style>
